content.text: The theory provides tools to work with this new understanding: - Operators that respect configuration - Metrics that capture spatial relationships - Algorithms that detect emergence - Equations that model indefiniteness As we explore this new mathematical landscape, we discover that the "problems" of traditional mathematics (paradoxes, infinities, undecidability) are actually features revealing the configurational nature of mathematical reality
